\
\'93By the way, where is Bill?\'94 Brett asked.\
\
\'93He\'92s out at Chantilly dining with some people.\'94\
\
\'93He\'92s a good chap.\'94\
\
\'93Splendid chap,\'94 said Mike. \'93He is, you know.\'94\
\
\'93You don\'92t remember him,\'94 Brett said.\
\
\'93I do. Remember him perfectly. Look, Jake, we\'92ll come down the night of\
the 25th. Brett can\'92t get up in the morning.\'94\
\
\'93Indeed not!\'94\
\
\'93If our money comes and you\'92re sure you don\'92t mind.\'94\
\
\'93It will come, all right. I\'92ll see to that.\'94\
\
\'93Tell me what tackle to send for.\'94\
\
\'93Get two or three rods with reels, and lines, and some flies.\'94\
\
\'93I won\'92t fish,\'94 Brett put in.\
\
\'93Get two rods, then, and Bill won\'92t have to buy one.\'94\
\
\'93Right,\'94 said Mike. \'93I\'92ll send a wire to the keeper.\'94\
\
\'93Won\'92t it be splendid,\'94 Brett said. \'93Spain! We _will_ have fun.\'94\
\
\'93The 25th. When is that?\'94\
\
\'93Saturday.\'94\
\
\'93We _will_ have to get ready.\'94\
\
\'93I say,\'94 said Mike, \'93I\'92m going to the barber\'92s.\'94\
\
\'93I must bathe,\'94 said Brett. \'93Walk up to the hotel with me, Jake. Be a\
good chap.\'94\
\
\'93We _have_ got the loveliest hotel,\'94 Mike said. \'93I think it\'92s a\
