In our compartment were a man and his wife and their young son.\
\
\'93I suppose you\'92re Americans, aren\'92t you?\'94 the man asked. \'93Having a good\
trip?\'94\
\
\'93Wonderful,\'94 said Bill.\
\
\'93That\'92s what you want to do. Travel while you\'92re young. Mother and I\
always wanted to get over, but we had to wait a while.\'94\
\
\'93You could have come over ten years ago, if you\'92d wanted to,\'94 the wife\
said. \'93What you always said was: \'91See America first!\'92 I will say we\'92ve\
