\'93So, that\'92s what they are. Pilgrims. Goddam Puritans,\'94 Bill said.\
\
\'93What part of the States you boys from?\'94\
\
\'93Kansas City,\'94 I said. \'93He\'92s from Chicago.\'94\
\
\'93You both going to Biarritz?\'94\
\
\'93No. We\'92re going fishing in Spain.\'94\
\
\'93Well, I never cared for it, myself. There\'92s plenty that do out where I\
come from, though. We got some of the best fishing in the State of\
Montana. I\'92ve been out with the boys, but I never cared for it any.\'94\
\
\'93Mighty little fishing you did on them trips,\'94 his wife said.\
\
He winked at us.\
\
\'93You know how the ladies are. If there\'92s a jug goes along, or a case of\
beer, they think it\'92s hell and damnation.\'94\
\
\'93That\'92s the way men are,\'94 his wife said to us. She smoothed her\
